@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml

top to bottom direction
title FIG-08-06. Horizon Bank payment instruction data lifecycle

skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam nodesep 45
skinparam ranksep 45

rectangle "Captured\nSystem: Horizon Digital Channels\nAuthoritative input: customer submission" as Captured #EAF6E8
rectangle "Validated\nSystem: Payments Platform\nAuthoritative status: validation result" as Validated #EAF6E8
rectangle "Screened\nSystem: Financial Crime Platform\nAuthoritative input: screening result" as Screened #FFF4D6
rectangle "Posted\nSystem: Core Deposit System\nAuthoritative input: posting result" as Posted #FFF4D6
rectangle "Distributed\nSystem: Event Platform\nAuthoritative event: consolidated payment status" as Distributed #F1E8FA
rectangle "Curated\nSystem: Enterprise Data Platform\nOwner: data product team" as Curated #F2F5F7
rectangle "Retained\nOwner: records policy\nRetention and audit obligations" as Retained #FFFFFF
rectangle "Archived or Disposed\nOwner: records policy\nArchive or defensible disposal" as Archived #FFFFFF

Captured --> Validated
Validated --> Screened
Screened --> Posted
Posted --> Distributed
Distributed --> Curated
Curated --> Retained
Retained --> Archived

note bottom
  Data lifecycle view.
  It shows state, responsible system or owner, and where authoritative status is established.
  It excludes detailed repair workflow, payment scheme rules and physical archive design.
end note
@enduml
